page.title: 06ECOLOGY
page.content: There is only one village in our block. It is called Beeley. In Beeley there is a house called the Norman House. The fields around are mostly farmlands. There are quite a few woodlands as well. Our block starts on an old railway and one of the edges is Chatsworth weir. We had our dinner on Chatsworth. Then we went in a private wood, the trees in this wood were deciduous trees. We went through somebodys garden because a man had let us. We went through some fields. There was a field of mud where they had been ploughing the field. We went through another wood which was also deciduous trees.There is a wood in our block it is called Smeltingmill Wood.It has got massive walls in it they could be hundreds of years old We found out it is also a quarry.......
